briefdescription.para: Any mapping schema from S to error codes convenient on *nix can be used.
Not enough memory to complete the operation.
Insufficient system resources exist to complete the operation.
An invalid parameter was passed to a function.
An item already exists. For example, create a route which already exists.
An item was not found. For example, remove a route which does not exist.
The data was too large to fit into the specified buffer.
Invalid SAI Object type passed to a function.

detaileddescription.para: If the object id is passed as an attribute value in list, then SAI_STATUS_INVALID_ATTR_VALUE_0 status code should be used.

briefdescription.para: Invalid SAI Object ID passed to a function.

detaileddescription.para: Return SAI_STATUS_INVALID_OBJECT_TYPE when the object type is invalid, otherwise return this SAI_STATUS_INVALID_OBJECT_ID. This can happen if the object id is already deleted.

briefdescription.para: The NV storage used is either invalid or corrupt. (rv for initialize_switch())
The NV storage is full. (rv for shutdown_switch())
Version mismatch in case of Inservice upgrade (rv for initialize_switch())

detaileddescription.para: Return this when the property attached to the attribute does not match the API call.

For example:
When a READ_ONLY attribute is passed set_attribute or create call
When a CREATE_ONLY attribute is passed to set_attribute call
The offset from SAI_STATUS_INVALID_ATTRIBUTE_0 is the array index of the attribute list passed to the SAI API call.

briefdescription.para: End of invalid attribute value range.

detaileddescription.para: Return this when the attribute is supported but not implemented on the platform.
Return this when the attribute is undefined, e.g., the attribute id is out of range.
Return this when the platform does not have the capability to support this attribute.

briefdescription.para: End of attribute not supported range.
This module defines SAI Status codes.
